Many doubt that a half increase will bring the same fruits as the increase in Iraq.
Despite the fratricidal wars of recent years, Iraqi society is relatively well organized and its leaders honor the agreements.
The Afghan situation stands out by the exact opposite - no one can be counted on and no treaty is respected.
Under these conditions, it is difficult to prepare Afghan security forces, accustomed to changing leaders day by day according to what is convenient to them.
Political institutions, although officially founded, will remain only powder in the eyes behind which patriarchal ethnic relations will proliferate.
It is particularly complex to balance the interests of the various ethnic groups in view of the lack of clarity on the relationship, which is still complicated by Pakistani and Iranian influences.
Even the foundation of a "quick state to act", which is the basic purpose of the operation, does not seem to be very real.
The time horizon of Obama’s strategy is perplexed by his voluntarism.
In the last eight years, the situation in Afghanistan has only worsened and is currently on the brink of chaos.
Only a purely romantic and out of reality heart can be convinced that the little soldiers sent into the tumult of the war for their "prompt return home" will bring there a real miracle.
From a political point of view, setting a date for the withdrawal of troops is purely irresponsible since the Taliban will see it as an indirect admission of American defeat.
The latest NATO summit showed that the willingness of Europeans to participate in military operations in Afghanistan is oriented towards the negative.
European politicians do not know or want to explain to their constituents how security in Germany or Italy is linked to a war in the Hindu Kush mountains.
Another factor capable of radically altering the situation is the development of events related to Iran.
If the situation continues to deteriorate and the increased sanctions have no effect on the Iranians, the Americans will find themselves faced with the very difficult issue of resolving the problem through the use of military force.
We will have to respond to this, for example, at a time when, according to Obama, America will come to the victorious withdrawal of troops from Afghanistan.
Any such solution will, however, bring about a dramatic reversal of the Afghan situation.
The only hardship for Obama is the fact that there are three years left until the presidential election and therefore there is still enough time for him to work on a new strategy, in case it turns out to be a total fiasco.
