How much should you be paid based on your Facebook profile?
Facebook users can know the salary they would deserve based on their profile, thanks to a new app from Trovit, the search engine with the largest number of real estate listings, jobs and vehicles in Spain.
The “How much should you be paid?” tool calculates the salaries of users from more than 140,000 job offers Trovit has in Spain, from a form available on Facebook, where you must register your profession, your years of experience, your age and the city where you want to work.
For the past week, the search engine has detected that, as a rule, the Spanish worker “feels badly paid,” Trovit’s product manager Albert Ribera said in a statement.
According to data available to Trovit from its search engines in the UK and France, Spaniards are the lowest paid.
A British computer programmer receives 45,226 euros gross annually and a French one, 31,059, while a Spanish one receives 24,000 euros.
Similarly, a driver receives 34,247 euros gross per year in England, 25,751 euros gross per year in France and 16,420 euros gross per year in Spain.
According to Trovit, the lowest paid work in Spain is that of a waiter, with 11 592 euros per year, followed by that of a seller, with 14 725 euros, and that of a worker, with 15 667 euros.
The most searched jobs on the Internet in the last three months are that of a driver, part-time jobs and social worker.
